condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Maintenance arrangements description: Recipient shall cause TRC to provide maintenance provision arrangementsfor the railway infrastructure assets in a manner satisfactory to the Association. Due Date: December 31, 2019

Recipient shall cause LATRA and TRC to (i) adopt implementing regulations and procedures for the full implementation of an OpenAccess Rail Policy in form and substance satisfactory to the Association; and (ii) implement said regulations and procedures toallow qualified operators to use the Dar es Salaam-Isaka line under licenses issued by SUMATRA and access by TRC. Due Date: June30, 2020

TRC Business Plan: Recipient shall (i) develop a five year business plan for TRC, satisfactory to the Association; (ii) take allnecessary measures to enable and cause TRC to implement the business plan; and (iii) review the status of implementation and takemeasures to ensure continued effective execution of the business plan to achieve the Project objective. Due Date: December 31, 2019

The Recipient shall not transfer the assets financed under Part B of the Project to TRC for its operations, until that: theRecipient has completed its review of TRC's implementation of its three year business plan as described in paragraph 50 (b)-(i) ofthe PAD (and paragraph D. 2 of Schedule 2, Section I of the FA) and the Association is satisfied with the review. Due date May 31,2020
